summary: hello can you write a fic where buffy still hates tj and tyrus is dating and buffy says something not nice and cyrus defends his...
question: hello can you write a fic where buffy still hates tj and tyrus is dating and buffy says something not nice and cyrus defends his bf and idk why but i really want this
answer:
sure! It’s short, super short, but like ????? how do i keep going????

Cyrus sat down n a booth across from Andi and Buffy, panting slightly.

“Hey, guys! Sorry I’m a little late, I slept over at TJ’s and we were up until like 4 am-” Andi and Buffy raised their eyebrows suggestively. “No! Stop thinking terrible things! we were playing Mario Kart! Anyway, we slept in and by the time I woke up I only had thirty minutes to get here, so I ran.”

“You slept over at TJ’s again? You said you were busy when we asked to hang out last night,” Buffy said, frustrated. 

“I was busy! I already had plans with TJ, and I didn’t want to cancel,” Cyrus defended.

“That makes sense to me,” Andi added, taking a sip from her milkshake.

“Yeah, but you’ve been spending all your time with TJ! It’s like you’ve forgotten we exist!” Buffy spluttered.

“That’s not fair, I still see you two literally every day! And he’s my boyfriend!” Cyrus exclaimed.

“For someone who’s not good enough for you, you sure think highly of him,” Buffy muttered, angrily drinking from her milkshake.

“Hey! That’s not fair! You have a right to be mad at him for how he treated you, but who is and isn’t good enough for me is not your call to make! TJ Kippen is my boyfriend, whether you like it or not. And we’re happy together. You don’t get to be mad because TJ and I love each other and you don’t like him!” Cyrus huffed, getting up and walking out of the Spoon.

For a while, Andi and Buffy sat in silence, before Andi opened her mouth to say something.

“He’s right, you know,” she said. A sad expression came over Buffy’s face.

“Yeah, I know.”

summary: 3 New Disney Channel Shows Will Soon Join Andi Mack
title: 3 New Disney Channel Shows Will Soon Join Andi Mack
body:
by spaceotter42

Three new live action Disney Channel shows will soon premiere to replace the departing Stuck In The Middle, which ended in July after three seasons, plus Bunk’d and Bizaardvark, which are near the end of their three-year runs.

“Coop & Cami Ask the World” will premiere Friday, October 12 on Disney Channel.  According to DC PR on Twitter, the live action comedy series is “about a brother and sister who make all of their decisions by crowdsourcing opinions from followers of the brother’s online channel.”  It stars Dakota Lotus and Ruby Rose Turner as the title characters.

“Gabby Duran & the Unsittables” has been commissioned as a straight-to-series order.  According to Variety, it stars Kylie Cantrall, and the “sci-fi series centers on Cantrall’s Gabby, who just landed a gig babysitting alien children from outer space and must now add intergalactic protector to her list of childcare responsibilities.”  There’s no date yet set for this series premiere.

“Fast Layne” has been greenlighted by Disney Channel, according to Deadline. “Twelve-year-old overachiever Layne (The Young and the Restless actress Sophie Pollono) finds her orderly life thrown into a tailspin when she discovers a sophisticated talking car named V.I.N. hidden in an abandoned shed. With the help of her eccentric neighbor, Zora (Sofia Rosinsky), Layne embarks on a high-speed adventure filled with bad guys, secret agents and other surprises to unlock the mystery behind V.I.N.’s creation.”  This series has no start date yet.

The three new shows will join the returning Andi Mack and Raven’s Home on Disney Channel’s schedule.

@persongoingfast
